== General energy storage concepts == 1. Using a high density magnetic field. Energy <math>E</math> in terms of magnetic field strength <math>B</math> is
<math>E = \frac{1}{2}B^2 = \frac{1}{2}Li^2</math>
where <math>L</math> is the inductance of the electromagnet and <math>i</math> is the current.
